The newspaper Aktuálně.cz has a bit of a "knockdown" on members of the new Council from the ČSSD, as they master the notorious snake that has become popular in recent years, when the current coalition partners in Prague were at the helm.
The coded vocabulary introduced by the Prague political elite in the late era of Mayor Pavel Bém borrows from some of the most well-known actors, situations and causes.
Surprisingly, the new councils were somewhat shady in their use of these new terms.
At least that's what they say.
"Who is Voldemort?"
"I don't know".
