In a double bed, everyone needs their own roast and mattress, but be careful when shopping to keep the mattresses the same height.
Otherwise, the only thing left is to mount the bed in different heights, and this is not possible with every bed frame.
Foam mattresses should be at least 14 cm high, and feathered mattresses 15 cm high, with at least 3 cm of this on the molding layer and the fine cushion.
"You must not feel the feathers with your hand or when you put them on", warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a specific type of roast.
Full-covered beds with mattresses and underpants like twins of a litter have nothing to look for in the bedroom.
These mattresses cannot be ventilated and the connection cannot be washed, which is already common today.
And since you lose between 0.2 and 0.75 liters of sweat in one night, it's clear that after five to seven years, the mattress slowly becomes a huge (and clogged) seabed.
This is why professionals reject advertising slogans that promise mattresses a lifetime of up to 25 years, even a lifetime guarantee.
Every thing has its If and But.
And that is why a practical advice from the merchants: For mattresses that are 120 or 140 centimeters wide, you should not be afraid of the hygiene of the washable, removable covers, yet it is advisable to use a mattress cleaner that can be easily removed and washed.
Although today mattress covers are usually made with a round-breasted seal, so that when opened you get two halves (especially important for the washing process and the size of the washing machine!), the manipulation of larger mattresses, especially by yourself, often seems to be the uneven battle between David and Goliath.
Do they have a plate in bed instead of a roast?
Get that out of here!
Or at most, a bed for unloved guests and for one night.
They should also be fitted with ventilation holes (if none are already in) and use mattresses with feathered skeletons and a minimum height of 15 cm with so-called pocket feathers and fine cushions.
Polyurethane mattresses are not included in such a substrate.
Latex or sandwich mats (including combinations of latex and coconut) are suitable for non-adjustable latex mats with 14 to 18 feathered bars (lamels), whereas a larger number of latex mats, i.e. 28 or more feathered bars, with a loose support in the lumbar vertebrae area and the possibility of regulating the lattice hardness, always pay off.
